02/20/84  copy_as_meters

Syntax:  copy_as_meters path


Function: This command is executed by the crank (in master.ec), which
is usually run once each day, to enable statistical tools to analyze
the system's performance.  It copies the system metering information
maintained by as_meter_ from the segment >sc1>stat_seg into a
specified data segment, and resets the index in stat_seg.  The
system_total command uses the segment created by the copy_as_meters
command.


Arguments:
path
   is the pathname of the copy to be created into which the statistics
   are placed.
